      </div>
      <p>
      I found
      myself agreeing with her most of the times, except that I did not
      quite like her excessive use of commas as well as her weird enthusiasm
      for colons and semi-colons. I learnt a fair bit about punctuation
      conventions and realised that I have been guilty of abusing
      punctuation on numerous occasions myself. I liked her sense of humour
      a lot and being a stickler for such things myself, empathised with her
      when she noted her anguish on seeing numerous abuses of punctuation
      all around her every day.

